paragraphs.text: %md # How it Works In order to simplify the management of two "physical" Neo4j instances we will leverage the Neo4j 4.0 multi-tennancy feature: So we have two databases: * `cdcschemasource`: push the CDC events to Kafka * `cdcschematarget`: pulls the CDC events from Kafka and reconstruct the original graph structure

msg.data:
How it Works

In order to simplify the management of two “physical” Neo4j instances we will leverage the Neo4j 4.0 multi-tennancy feature:

So we have two databases:

  • cdcschemasource: push the CDC events to Kafka
  • cdcschematarget: pulls the CDC events from Kafka and reconstruct the original graph structure

paragraphs.text:
%md
# Docker configuration

In the Docker Compose file you'll find the following configuration

```
NEO4J_streams_source_topic_nodes_cdcschematopic_from_cdcschemasource: Person{*};Movie{*}
NEO4J_streams_source_topic_relationships_cdcschematopic_from_cdcschemasource: ACTED_IN{*};DIRECTED{*};PRODUCED{*};WROTE{*};FOLLOWS{*};REVIEWED{*}
NEO4J_streams_sink_topic_cdc_schema_to_cdcschematarget: cdcschematopic
```

The first two lines describe where the `Source` module must push the data, and the thirs configure the topic and the target database in order to consume that data

paragraphs.text: %md # The Dataset In order to show this feature we will use the Neo4j Movie graph that can be found by typing `:play movies` inside the Neo4j browser. After ingested the data we will expect to have the following graph structure on both `cdcschemasource` and `cdcschematarget` databases:

msg.data:
The Dataset

In order to show this feature we will use the Neo4j Movie graph that can be found by typing :play movies inside the Neo4j browser.

After ingested the data we will expect to have the following graph structure on both cdcschemasource and cdcschematarget databases:

paragraphs.text:
%neo4j_cdcschemasource
CREATE CONSTRAINT kafka_cdc_movie_constr ON (m:Movie) ASSERT (m.title) IS UNIQUE

%neo4j_cdcschemasource
CREATE CONSTRAINT kafka_cdc_person_constr ON (p:Person) ASSERT (p.name) IS UNIQUE

table.tableOptionSpecHash: [{"name":"useFilter","valueType":"boolean","defaultValue":false,"widget":"checkbox","description":"Enable filter for columns"},{"name":"showPagination","valueType":"boolean","defaultValue":false,"widget":"checkbox","description":"Enable pagination for better navigation"},{"name":"showAggregationFooter","valueType":"boolean","defaultValue":false,"widget":"checkbox","description":"Enable a footer for displaying aggregated values"}]

paragraphs.text:
%neo4j_cdcschematarget
CREATE CONSTRAINT kafka_cdc_movie_constr ON (m:Movie) ASSERT (m.title) IS UNIQUE

%neo4j_cdcschematarget
CREATE CONSTRAINT kafka_cdc_person_constr ON (p:Person) ASSERT (p.name) IS UNIQUE
